","1050–1086":"1050–1086","–Male":"Overleden","0980–1031":"0980–1031","1003–1035":"1003–1035","1066":"1066","1099":"1099","1031":"1031","1086":"1086","1050":"1050","1049":"1049","1025":"1025","1003":"1003","1035":"1035","1024":"1024","0980":"0980","1100":"1100","22 July 1035":"22 juli 1035","Grestain, Eure, Haute-Normandie, France":"Carbec-Grestain, Eure, Haute-Normandie, Frankrijk","Linton, Herefordshire, England":"Linton, Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Cleuville, Seine-Inferieure, Normandy, France":"Cleuville, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Frankrijk","Bladleslane, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1025–1066":"1025–1066","1024–1099":"1024–1099","1050–1100":"1050–1100","1050–1086":"1050–1086","–Male":"Deceased","0980–1031":"0980–1031","1003–1035":"1003–1035","1066":"1066","1099":"1099","1031":"1031","1086":"1086","1050":"1050","1049":"1049","1025":"1025","1003":"1003","1035":"1035","1024":"1024","0980":"0980","1100":"1100","22 July 1035":"22 July 1035","Grestain, Eure, Haute-Normandie, France":"Carbec-Grestain, Eure, Upper Normandy, France","Linton, Herefordshire, England":"Linton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Cleuville, Seine-Inferieure, Normandy, France":"Cleuville, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France","Bladleslane, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Talbot","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Marcel, Anatole, Armand, Aubert, Camille, Gilles, Normand, Adrien, Alcide, Andre, Auguste.","English and Irish (of Norman origin); French: from the Anglo-Norman French personal name <i>Talebot</i>, a pet form of Old French <i>Talebert</i>, <i>Talbert</i> (see   Talbert   1). Compare   Talbert   2.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Talbald</i>, composed of the elements <i>dal</i> ‘bright, proud’ or <i>tal</i> ‘valley’ + <i>bald</i> ‘bold’."],"variants":[{"name":"Talbert","meanings":["English and Scottish (of Norman origin); French: from the Old French personal name <i>Talebert</i>, <i>Talbert</i>, from ancient Germanic <i>Talaberht</i> or <i>Dalbert</i>, composed of the elements <i>dal</i> ‘bright, proud’ or <i>tal</i> ‘valley’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright’.","Altered form of English   Talbot  , a cognate of 1 above."]},{"name":"Talbott","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Talbot  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William de Talbot was born in 1025, in Cleuville, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France, his father, Lesire Talbot Of Battleden, was 45 and his mother, Herleva d'Evereux, was 22. He married Basilia de Fleitel in 1049, in Linton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1066, in Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1025–1066":"1025–1066","1024–1099":"1024–1099","1050–1100":"1050–1100","1050–1086":"1050–1086","–Male":"Surnud","0980–1031":"0980–1031","1003–1035":"1003–1035","1066":"1066","1099":"1099","1031":"1031","1086":"1086","1050":"1050","1049":"1049","1025":"1025","1003":"1003","1035":"1035","1024":"1024","0980":"0980","1100":"1100","22 July 1035":"22. juuli 1035","Grestain, Eure, Haute-Normandie, France":"Carbec-Grestain, Eure, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Linton, Herefordshire, England":"Linton, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cleuville, Seine-Inferieure, Normandy, France":"Cleuville, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Bladleslane, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1025–1066":"1025–1066","1024–1099":"1024–1099","1050–1100":"1050–1100","1050–1086":"1050–1086","–Male":"Kuollut","0980–1031":"0980–1031","1003–1035":"1003–1035","1066":"1066","1099":"1099","1031":"1031","1086":"1086","1050":"1050","1049":"1049","1025":"1025","1003":"1003","1035":"1035","1024":"1024","0980":"0980","1100":"1100","22 July 1035":"22. heinäkuuta 1035","Grestain, Eure, Haute-Normandie, France":"Carbec-Grestain, Eure, Haute-Normandie, Ranska","Linton, Herefordshire, England":"Linton, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cleuville, Seine-Inferieure, Normandy, France":"Cleuville, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Ranska","Bladleslane, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1025–1066":"1025–1066","1024–1099":"1024–1099","1050–1100":"1050–1100","1050–1086":"1050–1086","–Male":"Décédé","0980–1031":"0980–1031","1003–1035":"1003–1035","1066":"